# Schema changes (required reading)

Before adding or modifying any schema or related code in this repo, **read and follow** these guides end-to-end:

- **New schema**: `docs/adding_schemas.md` (full checklist: JSON schema, changelog, type class, mappings, search config, fixtures, inserts, type tests, `loadxl.py`, `conftest.py`, etc.)
- **Existing schema**: `docs/updating_schemas.md` (property guidelines, changelog stylebook, when to bump `schema_version`, upgrades, tests, inserts)

Do not skip steps because a change “looks small.” Use the doc checklists as the source of truth.

## Decision: new vs update

| Situation | Primary doc |
|-----------|-------------|
| New item type / new `*.json` under `schemas/` | `docs/adding_schemas.md` |
| Edit existing schema, mixin, audit, upgrade, or inserts | `docs/updating_schemas.md` |

`updating_schemas.md` points to `adding_schemas.md` for brand-new types.

## Minimum touch points (updates)

When changing an existing schema, verify against `docs/updating_schemas.md`:

1. `src/igvfd/schemas/{name}.json` — property rules (title, description, array `minItems`/`uniqueItems`, etc.)
2. `src/igvfd/schemas/changelogs/{name}.md` — stylebook entries; version bump vs “minor changes since…”
3. `src/igvfd/types/` — calculated properties, embedding, reverse links
4. `src/igvfd/upgrade/` — if `schema_version` bump invalidates existing objects
5. `src/igvfd/searches/configs/` — if search columns/facets change
6. `src/igvfd/tests/data/inserts/` and `src/igvfd/tests/` — validation tests
7. `src/igvfd/mappings/` — regenerate after schema/calculated/embedded changes (see `README.md`; run via Docker per `docker-testing` rule)

## Minimum touch points (new schemas)

Follow every **REQUIRED** row in `docs/adding_schemas.md` summary table (abstract vs concrete differs).

## Audits

New validation rules belong in `src/igvfd/audit/` with docstrings for audit metadata; register in the type’s dispatcher. Run tests in Docker (`docker-testing` rule).

## Tests

- Type/schema tests: `docker compose -f docker-compose.test.yml run --rm pyramid pytest …`
- Do not use host `pytest` / conda for this repo
